Dartford Grammar School – Year 8 Maths

Test Paper: Pythagoras, Area, Volume, Circumference
Time: 60 minutes
Instructions:

Show all working.

Give answers to 1 decimal place where appropriate.

Use π ≈ 3.14 unless instructed otherwise.

Section A: Pythagoras (Questions 1–8)

A right-angled triangle has legs of length 6 cm and 8 cm. Find the length of the hypotenuse.

A ladder 5 m long leans against a wall. The bottom of the ladder is 3 m from the wall. How high does the ladder reach?

The hypotenuse of a right triangle is 13 cm, and one leg is 5 cm. Find the other leg.

A rectangular field measures 50 m by 120 m. Find the length of the diagonal.

A right triangle has one leg measuring 7 cm and the hypotenuse 25 cm. Find the length of the other leg.

A square has a diagonal of 10√2 cm. Find the length of one side.

A right triangle has legs in the ratio 3:4. If the hypotenuse is 25 cm, find the lengths of the legs.

A kite has diagonals of 10 cm and 24 cm. One of the triangles formed is right-angled. Find the length of the diagonal across the right angle.

Section B: Area of Shapes (Questions 9–14)

Find the area of a triangle with base 12 cm and height 9 cm.

A trapezium has parallel sides 8 cm and 14 cm and a height of 5 cm. Find its area.

A rectangle has length 15 cm and width 7 cm. Find its area.

A circle has a radius of 7 cm. Find its area.

A sector of a circle has a central angle of 60° and radius 10 cm. Find the area of the sector.

Find the area of a semicircle with diameter 12 cm.

Section C: Volume (Questions 15–20)

A cube has a side of 5 cm. Find its volume.

A cuboid has length 10 cm, width 6 cm, and height 4 cm. Find its volume.

A cylinder has a radius of 3 cm and height 10 cm. Find its volume.

A cone has a radius of 4 cm and height 9 cm. Find its volume.

A sphere has a radius of 6 cm. Find its volume.

A prism has a triangular base with base 5 cm, height 8 cm, and prism height 12 cm. Find its volume.

Section D: Circumference & Perimeter (Questions 21–25)

Find the circumference of a circle with a radius of 8 cm.

A circular garden has a diameter of 14 m. Find its circumference.

A semi-circular path has a radius of 7 m. Find the length of the path.

The perimeter of a sector of a circle with radius 10 cm and angle 90° is required. Find it.

A circular pond has a radius of 5 m. A fence is built around it. Find the length of the fence needed.
